## Node tests (nix_node_test)

- This scaffold includes a hermetic Node test target by default (`nix_node_test(name = "unit", ...)`) powered by a Nix‑backed Vitest runner.
- Opt out of sample tests and devDependencies with `--no-tests` (the test target remains and passes when no tests match):

```bash
scaf new ts {{ template }} {{ name }} --yes --no-tests
```

- Default discovery patterns:
  - `test/**/*.test.(ts|js)`
  - `__tests__/**/*.test.(ts|js)`
  - `src/**/*.test.(ts|js)`

### Coverage and timeouts

- Coverage: enable per run with `COVERAGE=1 buck2 test //<pkg>:unit -- --env COVERAGE=1`.
- Timeout: default 600s per test target; can be adjusted via the macro’s `timeout_sec`.

### Troubleshooting

- If tests match patterns but Vitest isn’t in devDependencies, the runner fails with a clear message. Add `vitest` and re-run.
- If no tests match, the runner passes (useful while bootstrapping).
